Moral uncertainty binds

    - The normative ethic here developed takes its ground in moral uncertainty.
    - It applies to any rational agent who cannot reasonably hold belief Mb.

        Mb. My knowledge of what violable norms are morally binding on me excludes none
          that I might learn of.



    M. Moral certainty.
        - M means reasonably holding belief Mb.
    H. Humanity extant through to M.
        - Humanity continues to exist while M is unachieved.


